<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5399959>
    dc:description "FIG. 25. — Ethusina robusta (Miers, 1886); A, lectotype cl 10.0 mm, cw 10.1 mm, Challenger, stn 191, Arafura Sea, 1463 m (BMNH 84.44), dorsal surface of carapace and P2; B, C, cl 8.6 mm, cw 8.2 mm, Solomon Islands, east of Malaita, SALOMON 1, stn CP 1764, 1327-1598 m (MNHN-B 28712); B, left G1, dorsal view; C, left G2, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, 5 mm; B, C, 1 mm." ;
